        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/{size}/31625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-04-11T09:57:21.028Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-top_contributors\" data-username=\"Whatnoww\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"60128\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/whatnoww/48/54328_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Whatnoww:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I don’t think Signal would be willing to implement a security feature that is so easily “workaroundable” at a technical level.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>and in fact, if I remember correctly, the very first pre-staging versions of PnP had “contacts” as an option, and that eventually got removed.</p>",
