        "name": "",
        "username": "bjoel",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/bjoel/{size}/32746_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-04-17T04:25:15.659Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This would leak your number to every number you search (and the fact that you searched for them).</p>\n<p>Even if you do this with zkp stuff, the server (and potential other users) could abuse it and leak contact lists.</p>\n<p>Edit.<br>\nmaybe some mpc impl where you send a message to that number containing the garbled circuit and the receiver can either just drop it (if they don’t have contact discovery turned on) or evaluate the circuit and if true sends back their number</p>\n<p>though this would require separate infrastructure to not reveal ACI or profile keys to requesters (and rely on an honest server)</p>",
