        "username": "MMachado05",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/mmachado05/{size}/49230_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-09T17:56:58.164Z",
        "cooked": "<p>If this feature is pretty much, “add an option where only those numbers that <em>I</em> have saved on my phone can see that I’m <em>also</em> on Signal,” I have to say I’d enjoy that very much. The current paradigm makes it a bit simple to “brute force” someone’s number, or at least discover it by chance, because if they have your number registered on their phone contacts and make a connection with you, they’ll also discover that <em>that’s your number.</em> This is a particularly valid use case because of mass texting schemes done by scam accounts, whereby they might save hundreds of numbers onto their device of choice, send out random messages, and then potentially learn a bit about the people who own those numbers. If instead you could only be reached out to by those with whom you have a <em>mutual</em> connection, this would really tighten up that security angle.</p>\n<p>But also, I’m not sure how this would be implemented, and other responses here seem to suggest that it really <em>can’t</em> be without other privacy compromises…</p>",
